        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Log previously swallowed exceptions",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Log exceptions that were previously swallowed in tray/setup flows.\n- Add recent sanitized tray log tail to the diagnostics/debug bundle.\n- Preserve safe user-facing error text while writing detailed exception information to `openclaw-tray.log`.\n- Sanitize sensitive tray log details before writing to tray text logs, diagnostics JSONL, and crash logs; the diagnostics bundle re-sanitizes as defense in depth.\n\n## Validation\n- Ran `./build.ps1` successfully.\n- Ran `dotnet test ./tests/OpenClaw.Shared.Tests/OpenClaw.Shared.Tests.csproj --no-restore` successfully.\n- Ran `dotnet test ./tests/OpenClaw.Tray.Tests/OpenClaw.Tray.Tests.csproj --no-restore` successfully.\n- Ran manual tray/gateway smoke test with local gateway on `ws://127.0.0.1:19001/`.\n- Verified tray connected to gateway and node came online.\n- Triggered known invalid gateway failure with `ws://127.0.0.1:9/`.\n- Confirmed UI showed safe generic failure text while detailed connection-refused errors were logged to `%LOCALAPPDATA%\\OpenClawTray\\openclaw-tray.log`.\n\n## Proof notes\nInvalid gateway failure generated log lines like:\n\n```text\nGateway connectivity probe failed for http://127.0.0.1:9: No connection could be made because the target machine actively refused it. (127.0.0.1:9)\nGateway /health connectivity probe failed for http://127.0.0.1:9: No connection could be made because the target machine actively refused it. (127.0.0.1:9)\n```\n\nDiagnostics bundle now includes a bounded sanitized Recent Tray Log section sourced from the same tray log.\r\n",
